      "name": "What drives property values in Runcorn?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Runcorn property values are driven by the suburb's strong school catchments including Runcorn State High School, its family-friendly character with good parks and community infrastructure, Pacific Motorway access for CBD and Gold Coast commuting, and its position in the southern corridor adjacent to Sunnybank's food precinct. Upgrader buyers from the inner south consistently target Runcorn for the combination of more space, school catchment access, and a manageable price point relative to the closer-in alternatives. Properties with good outdoor space, functional layouts, and solid school catchment position attract the strongest buyer competition." }
    },
