      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How long does it take to sell a home in Runcorn?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Well-priced Runcorn homes typically sell within 25 to 40 days. The suburb's upgrader buyer pool is consistent and motivated, and the Runcorn State High School catchment creates a time-sensitive buyer segment that moves decisively when a property confirms catchment and meets their space requirements. Correctly pricing against recent comparable sales in Runcorn and acknowledging what buyers are comparing it to in Sunnybank and Coopers Plains is the primary lever for a well-timed result." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the lifestyle like in Runcorn?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Runcorn offers a family-oriented suburban lifestyle approximately fifteen kilometres south of the Brisbane CBD. The suburb has good parks and community spaces, and the proximity to Sunnybank's celebrated food precinct adds lifestyle variety that residents value. Pacific Motorway access makes the CBD and Gold Coast practical commutes, and the suburb's established residential streets and family infrastructure give it a settled, community character. Runcorn is a suburb where families tend to stay once they arrive, which underpins the community quality that attracts upgrader buyers." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is my Runcorn home worth in 2026?",
