<!-- ===============================================
     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
================================================ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">The southern Brisbane suburb that families and upgraders pursue for its school catchments, spacious family homes, motorway access, and its position adjacent to Sunnybank that gives residents the food precinct and southern corridor lifestyle at a more accessible price point.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Runcorn sits approximately fifteen kilometres south of the Brisbane CBD, positioned in the southern residential corridor between Sunnybank and the outer southern suburbs. It is a suburb that families choose deliberately. The school catchment centred on Runcorn State High School is a primary driver of demand from families with teenagers or with secondary school enrolment on the horizon, and that school-oriented buyer pool is among the most motivated and consistent in the southern corridor. When a property clearly confirms catchment position and presents the space that families require, it draws focused attention from buyers who have done their research and are ready to act.
    </p>
