    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The upgrader buyer from the inner south is the defining demand profile in Runcorn. These are families who have outgrown a smaller inner-south property, who have been watching the southern corridor for a home that gives them the space, the outdoor area, and the school catchment they need, and who have arrived at Runcorn after concluding that it delivers on all three at a price that works. They understand the Pacific Motorway access to the CBD, the proximity to Sunnybank's food precinct, and what the Runcorn address represents relative to Sunnybank Hills and Calamvale alternatives. They are informed buyers who act when the right property appears.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The housing stock in Runcorn is predominantly post-war and 1980s detached family homes on reasonable blocks, with newer townhouses and units in pockets of the suburb. Properties that present well, have usable outdoor space, and sit in recognisable catchment streets attract the most consistent and competitive buyer pools. Sellers who understand the specific driver of demand in Runcorn are better positioned to prepare their property in a way that speaks directly to what those buyers are looking for.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
